title: Part A
stimulusHtml:
Select a point value to view scoring criteria, solutions, and/or examples to score the response.

To earn the point, the setup used to perform the calculation must be evident in the response. The following examples earn the point: y ′  ( 4 ) x ′  ( 4 ) =0.701, MathType@MTEF@5@5@@4885@ ln( 2+ 4 2 ) 1+ 4 2 , MathType@MTEF@5@5@@43D6@ or ln 18 17 . MathType@MTEF@5@5@@40CA@

Note: A response with an incorrect equation of the form “ function=constant MathType@MTEF@5@5@@4921@ ”, such as y ′  ( t ) x ′  ( t ) = ln( 18 ) 17 , MathType@MTEF@5@5@@4B96@ will not earn the point. However, such a response will be eligible for any points for similar errors in subsequent parts.

title: Part B
stimulusHtml:
Select a point value to view scoring criteria, solutions, and/or examples to score the response.

To earn any of these points, the setup used to perform the calculation must be evident in the response. For example, ( x ′  ( 4 ) ) 2 + ( y ′  ( 4 ) ) 2 =5.035 MathType@MTEF@5@5@@4DD2@ or 17+ ( ln 18 ) 2 MathType@MTEF@5@5@@4327@ earns the first point, and 〈 x ″ (4),   y ″ (4) 〉=〈 4 17 ,  4 9 〉 MathType@MTEF@5@5@@4FB1@ earns both the second and third points.

The second and third points can be earned independently.

If the acceleration vector is not presented as an ordered pair, the x- and y-components must be labeled.

If the components of the acceleration vector are reversed, the response does not earn either of the last 2 points.

A response which correctly calculates expressions for both x ″ (t)= t 1+ t 2 MathType@MTEF@5@5@@41F6@ and y ″ (t)= 2t 2+ t 2 , MathType@MTEF@5@5@@435E@ but which fails to evaluate both of these expressions at t=4, MathType@MTEF@5@5@+=feaagCart1ev2aqatCvAUfeBSjuyZL2yd9gzLbvyNv2CaerbuLwBLnhiov2DGi1BTfMBaeXatLxBI9gBaerbd9wDYLwzYbItLDharqqtubsr4rNCHbGeaGqiFC0pg9uqGrpepeea0dXdHaVhbbe9u8qqaqFr0xc9pk0xj9qqaqFj0dh9qq=xfr=JarFfpeea0=as0=fs0di9uqFr0=vr0=vr0db8meaabaqaciGacaGaaeqabaWaaeaaeaaakeaacaWG0bGaeyypa0JaaGinaiaacYcaaaa@3C69@ earns only 1 of the last 2 points.

An unsupported acceleration vector earns only 1 of the last 2 points.

title: Part C
stimulusHtml:
Select a point value to view scoring criteria, solutions, and/or examples to score the response.

For the first point, an integrand of ln( 2+ t 2 ) MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3FF3@ can appear in either an indefinite integral or an incorrect definite integral.

A definite integral with incorrect limits is not eligible for the answer point.

Similarly, an indefinite integral is not eligible for the answer point.

For the second point, the value for y(4) MathType@MTEF@5@5@+=feaagCart1ev2aqatCvAUfeBSjuyZL2yd9gzLbvyNv2CaerbuLwBLnhiov2DGi1BTfMBaeXatLxBI9gBaerbd9wDYLwzYbItLDharqqtubsr4rNCHbGeaGqiFC0pg9uqGrpepeea0dXdHaVhbbe9u8qqaqFr0xc9pk0xj9qqaqFj0dh9qq=xfr=JarFfpeea0=as0=fs0di9uqFr0=vr0=vr0db8meaabaqaciGacaGaaeqabaWaaeaaeaaakeaacaWG5bGaaiikaiaaisdacaGGPaaaaa@3C11@ must be added to a definite integral.

A response that reports the correct x-coordinate of the particle’s position at time t=6 MathType@MTEF@5@5@+=feaagCart1ev2aqatCvAUfeBSjuyZL2yd9gzLbvyNv2CaerbuLwBLnhiov2DGi1BTfMBaeXatLxBI9gBaerbd9wDYLwzYbItLDharqqtubsr4rNCHbGeaGqiFC0pg9uqGrpepeea0dXdHaVhbbe9u8qqaqFr0xc9pk0xj9qqaqFj0dh9qq=xfr=JarFfpeea0=as0=fs0di9uqFr0=vr0=vr0db8meaabaqaciGacaGaaeqabaWaaeaaeaaakeaacaWG0bGaeyypa0JaaGOnaaaa@3BBB@ as x (6)=x(4)+ ∫ 4 6 1+ t 2 dt =11.200 MathType@MTEF@5@5@@50C4@ (or 11.201 MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3D55@ ) instead of the y-coordinate, earns 2 out of the 3 points.

A response that earns the first point but not the second can earn the third point with an answer of 6.571 MathType@MTEF@5@5@+=feaagCart1ev2aqatCvAUfeBSjuyZL2yd9gzLbvyNv2CaerbuLwBLnhiov2DGi1BTfMBaeXatLxBI9gBaerbd9wDYLwzYbItLDharqqtubsr4rNCHbGeaGqiFC0pg9uqGrpepeea0dXdHaVhbbe9u8qqaqFr0xc9pk0xj9qqaqFj0dh9qq=xfr=JarFfpeea0=as0=fs0di9uqFr0=vr0=vr0db8meaabaqaciGacaGaaeqabaWaaeaaeaaakeaacaaI2aGaaiOlaiaaiwdacaaI3aGaaGymaaaa@3CA9@ (or 6.570 MathType@MTEF@5@5@+=feaagCart1ev2aqatCvAUfeBSjuyZL2yd9gzLbvyNv2CaerbuLwBLnhiov2DGi1BTfMBaeXatLxBI9gBaerbd9wDYLwzYbItLDharqqtubsr4rNCHbGeaGqiFC0pg9uqGrpepeea0dXdHaVhbbe9u8qqaqFr0xc9pk0xj9qqaqFj0dh9qq=xfr=JarFfpeea0=as0=fs0di9uqFr0=vr0=vr0db8meaabaqaciGacaGaaeqabaWaaeaaeaaakeaacaaI2aGaaiOlaiaaiwdacaaI3aGaaGimaaaa@3CA8@ ).

If the differential is missing:

· y ( 6 )= ∫ 4 6 ln( 2+ t 2 ) MathType@MTEF@5@5@@4914@ earns the first point and is eligible for the third.

· y ( 6 )= ∫ 4 6 ln( 2+ t 2 ) +y ( 4 ) MathType@MTEF@5@5@@4ED6@ does not earn the first point but is eligible for the second and third points in the presence of the correct answer.

· y ( 6 )=y ( 4 )+ ∫ 4 6 ln( 2+ t 2 ) MathType@MTEF@5@5@@4ECB@ earns the first two points and is eligible for the third.

stimulusHtml:

To earn the second point, a response must have earned the first point and must present the value 12.136. MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3E2E@
